FASE - Fundamental Approaches to Software Engineering

Budapest (Hungary), March 29 - April 6, 2008

http://www.cs.le.ac.uk/events/fase2008/


FASE is concerned with the foundations on which Software Engineering =20
is built. Submissions should not focus on the application or =20
evaluation of given methods, tools or techniques for their own sake =20
but, rather, the principles on which they are based and the way in =20
which they contribute to making Software Engineering a more mature =20
and soundly-based discipline. Contributions that combine the =20
development of conceptual and methodological advances with their =20
formal foundations and tool support are particularly encouraged. We =20
welcome contributions on all such fundamental approaches, including:

=B7    SE as an engineering discipline, including its interaction with =20=

and impact on society;
=B7    Requirements engineering;
=B7    Domain modelling;
=B7    Software architectures;
=B7    Specification and design;
=B7    Engineering of particular classes of systems (e.g. =20
collaborative, service-oriented, software-intensive, ubiquitous);
=B7    Software processes;
=B7    Model-driven development;
=B7    Software evolution;
=B7    Validation and verification;
=B7    Testing.

Important Dates

5 October 2007: Submission deadline (strict) for abstracts of =20
research and tool demonstration papers
12 October 2007: Submission deadline (strict) for full versions of =20
research and tool demonstration papers


